      "title": "Google’s exponential path to climate-wrecking digital bloat",
      "url": "https://ketanjoshi.co/2026/07/01/googles-exponential-path-to-climate-wrecking-digital-bloat/",
      "discuss_url": "https://lobste.rs/s/v8hk8q",
      "score": 91,
      "comments": 9,
      "author": "sjamaan",
      "published": "2026-07-07T07:33:16Z",
      "bullets": [
        "Google's AI expansion, including Gemini integration, drove a 48% increase in greenhouse gas emissions over five years from data center energy.",
        "Training and running large language models exponentially increases compute requirements, challenging industry net-zero carbon goals and energy grid capacity.",
        "AI practitioners must prioritize energy-efficient model architectures, quantization, and green hosting to mitigate the environmental impact of scaling."
      ]
    },
    {
