      "score": 20,
      "comments": 1,
      "author": "markerz",
      "published": "2026-07-08T03:58:54Z",
      "bullets": [
        "Utilizes OpenType/TrueType font rendering engines to generate scannable 2D QR codes directly from text input without external APIs.",
        "Eliminates server-side rendering overhead and JavaScript dependencies, enabling offline QR code generation inside standard text processors.",
        "Uses complex OpenType GSUB ligature tables to assemble the QR matrix, offering a zero-code, zero-dependency alternative to QR libraries."
      ]
    },
    {
      "source": "lobsters",
      "subsource": "lobste.rs/security",
      "category": "security",
      "title": "OpenBSD through 7.9 has a use-after-free allowing local privilege escalation to root (CVE-2026-57589)",
      "url": "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/cve-2026-57589",
      "discuss_url": "https://lobste.rs/s/7hmu0w",
      "score": 16,
      "comments": 0,
      "author": "fro",
      "published": "2026-07-08T01:02:05Z",
      "bullets": [
        "Deployments of OpenBSD 7.9 and earlier must be audited immediately for CVE-2026-57589 to prevent complete host compromise.",
        "The memory safety flaw allows local, non-privileged users to bypass OS boundary controls and execute arbitrary commands as root.",
        "Remediation requires applying the latest official OpenBSD errata patches to eliminate this high-impact local privilege escalation vector."
      ]
    },
